.TH DESKTOP 1 "April 2026" "shaughvOS" "shaughvOS Commands"
.SH NAME
desktop \- toggle between desktop and console mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B desktop
.RI [ on | off | status ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B desktop
is a shaughvOS utility that switches between the graphical desktop
environment (Xfce) and console mode. Changes persist across reboots.
.PP
Requires root privileges to run.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B on
Switch to desktop mode with autologin. Starts the LightDM display
manager and sets the system to boot into the desktop on next reboot.
.TP
.B off
Switch to console mode with autologin. Stops the LightDM display
manager and sets the system to boot into a console on next reboot.
.TP
.B status
Display the current mode (Desktop or Console) and whether the
display manager is running.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-help
Display usage information.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Unknown command or error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shaughvos (1)
